article.headline: Winston-Salem St. 81, Norfolk St. 71
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Brian Fisher scored 20 points to lead Winston-Salem to a 81-71 win over Norfolk State on Thursday night. The win is the second straight for the Rams (3-18) after going on a 15-game losing streak that dates back to November. The Spartans (5-11) trailed 36-35 at halftime, whittling down a 31-15 lead for Winston-Salem midway through the first with a 20-4 run. The Rams took the lead early in the first period and never trailed, taking their largest lead of 59-39 with 12:31 to play. Darrell Wonge added 16 and Jamal Druham had 15 for Winston-Salem, who scored 27 points off turnovers. Calvin Brown had 20 points and 20 rebounds for Norfolk State and Tony Murphy added 20, helping him surpass 1,000 career points.
